txt.en: Lúkhag chirps in affirmation before leading you away from Annâk-khurfu.
Lúkhag hangs from a tree in front of Annâk-khurfu.\n\nYou should go to her and see where she'll lead you.
'You've returned, and in one piece! Aighrig doesn't seem to be herself, but I won't ask you what happened; she can tell me herself if she wishes.'
You should inform Rékkur of what you've learned about Gáfin's discovery.
Lúkhag chirps in affirmation before leading you away from Annâk-khurfu.\n\n<rgb=#FF0000>WARNING: This is a solo instance and cannot be completed in a fellowship.</rgb>
A frantic Lúkhag has returned without Aighrig.

'Lúkhag flew back while you were gone and pestered me to no end! I believe she wants to lead me somewhere, but I can't abandon my post, nor does she seem to trust anyone other than us.\n\n'Please follow her, [placeholder]. I have a feeling that you'll find Aighrig at the end of all this.'
